Summary: shiny metallic disc floating above the tree line near USF
divs: Sighting DetailsI was driving with my father West on Fletcher Ave. near the University of South Florida and I glimpsed a very shiny metallic disc with a slightly conical shape above the tree line by the time I realized I had seen anything it was gone. I didn't even think that I had seen anything unusual until I looked around for what it could be and nothing fit the profile. There is a water tower in the area but it is not metallic like the object I saw.
